        <bioghist id="ref10">
            <head>Biographical Note</head>
            <p>Dimitriĭ Petrovich Pershin was a White Russian diplomat in Mongolia from 1918 to 1921, a Russian historian and novelist, and subsequently a Russian émigré in China.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref11">
            <head>Scope and Content of Collection</head>
            <p>The collection consists of the writings of Pershin, as well as some correspondence and a small amount of biographical material. Among his writings is the memoir 
                <title render="italic">Baron Ungern, Urga i Altan-Bulak : Zapiski Ochevidtsa Smutnom Vremeni vo Vneshneĭ (Khakhaskoĭ) Mongoliĭ v Pervoĭ Treti II-go Veka</title>, based on his experiences in Siberia, the Transbaikal region of the Far East, and Mongolia between 1918 and 1921. The memoirs include notes, research materials, holographs, typescripts, and a final draft. The papers also include an English translation of the memoir by Russian-American historian Elena Varneck.</p>
        </scopecontent>
